{"body": "The name **cannot** be supplied through the block when using `link_to_if`/`link_to_unless`. From the docs:\r\n\r\n    To specialize the default behavior (i.e., show a login link rather\r\n    than just the plaintext link text), you can pass a block that\r\n    accepts the name or the full argument list for +link_to_unless+.\r\n\r\nWhich means the block has a very special behavior for these two helpers, that differ from the `link_to` usage. I believe the examples there can clarify this a bit more if necessary.\r\n\r\nThanks for your contribution!", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/12678099", "created_at": "2013-01-24T22:43:24Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/9066#issuecomment-12678099", "updated_at": "2013-01-24T22:43:24Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 9066, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/carlosantoniodasilva", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/77237b97a465ae5a293ad323b7296837?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F60b997fd68261ce70cadaf6c8226c042.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/received_events", "gravatar_id": "77237b97a465ae5a293ad323b7296837", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "carlosantoniodasilva", "type": "User", "id": 26328, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/followers"}, "owner": "rails